Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{2%unit}. Finely chop a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1%unit}. Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise, then cut crosswise into half-moons.

Toss together sliced shallot, bell pepper, zucchini, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{} on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} (divide between 2 foil-lined #baking sheets{} for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from oven; transfer veggies to a #medium bowl{}. Discard foil. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.

Dice @Roma tomato{1%unit}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve @lime{1%unit}. In a #small bowl{}, combine chopped shallot, tomato, cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon} (start with a pinch, taste, and add more from there if you like). Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Brush one side of each @flour tortillas{6%unit} with a drizzle of olive oil. Place half the tortillas on baking sheet used for veggies (for 4 servings, divide between 2 baking sheets), oiled sides down, and spread with chipotle mayo. Top with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup} and a few veggies (save some veggies for the salad). Top with remaining tortillas, oiled sides up.

Broil or bake quesadillas, flipping halfway through, until tortillas are crispy and cheese has melted, ~{1-2%minutes} per side (in batches for 4 servings).

> TIP: Watch carefully for any burning.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce} with remaining veggies, a squeeze of lime juice, a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Cut quesadillas into triangles. Top with pico de gallo. Serve salad on the side.